# MEMORY.md

This is the index of your persistent, file-based memory. Each memory is a single
markdown file in this directory holding one fact, with YAML frontmatter. This
index file is loaded into context each session — keep it to **one line per
memory**, never put memory content here.

Add a pointer when you create a memory:

```
- [Title](file.md) — short hook describing when it's relevant
```

## Memory types

- **user** — who the user is (role, expertise, durable preferences)
- **feedback** — guidance on how to work (corrections + confirmed approaches; include the *why*)
- **project** — ongoing work, goals, constraints not derivable from code/history (use absolute dates)
- **reference** — pointers to external resources (URLs, dashboards, tickets)

